{"meta":{"domain":"subjects","kid":"5095","authors":[{"fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre","id":"6"}],"title":"","dates":{"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:21 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:21 UTC"}},"nodes":[{"index":0,"parent_index":-1,"body":"<p class=\"Paragraph\">These indicate the future, and are practically the same as <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b<\/span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span>, but with more of a sense of obligation. The forms <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b<\/span> and <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f61\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b<\/span> are egophoric, whereas <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span> and <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f61\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span> are neutral. The verb that precedes the auxiliary should be in the present-future.<\/p><ul> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f51\u0f74\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f66\u0fb3\u0f7c\u0f56\u0f0b\u0f42\u0fb2\u0fad\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f66\u0f62\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0d<\/span> \u201cNext year, we have to build a new school.\u201d<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0f53\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f61\u0f62\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0d<\/span> \u201cWe have to find accommodation.\u201d<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f63\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f7a\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f55\u0f7a\u0f56\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f66\u0f0d<\/span> \u201cDo you have to leave immediately?\u201d<\/li> <\/ul><p class=\"Paragraph\">In certain contexts, the forms <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b<\/span> and <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span> may also imply that something that ought to have been done already has yet to be accomplished. In this case, it may be translated by \u201chasn\u2019t yet done X\u201d or \u201chas still to do X.\u201d The verb preceding the auxiliary must be in the present-future.<\/p><ul> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f41\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f5f\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0d<\/span> \u201cI haven\u2019t eaten yet.\u201d (I\u2019m about to eat.) <\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f41\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f68\u0f0b\u0f45\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f63\u0fb7\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f9f\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0d<\/span> \u201cHe has yet to go to the opera.\u201d<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f41\u0fb1\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f66\u0fa6\u0fb2\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f41\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f55\u0f7a\u0f56\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0d<\/span> \u201cYou still have to go to the post office.\u201d<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f72\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f62\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f9f\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0d<\/span> \u201cI haven\u2019t yet read today\u2019s newspaper.\u201d<\/li> <\/ul><p class=\"Paragraph\"><em>Note<\/em>: The suffixes <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b<\/span> and <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f61\u0f42\u0f0b<\/span> are usually interchangeable, but not in all cases. A distinction must be made between their function as nominalizing suffixes and as auxiliaries.<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\"><em>Nominalizing Suffixes<\/em>:<\/p><ul> <li>The patient: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b<\/span> (future) and <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f61\u0f42\u0f0b<\/span> (present or future)<\/li> <li>The instrument: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f61\u0f42\u0f0b<\/span> but not *<span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b<\/span><\/li> <li>The substance: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b<\/span> and <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f61\u0f42\u0f0b<\/span><\/li> <\/ul><p class=\"Paragraph\"><em>Auxiliaries<\/em>:<\/p><ul> <li>\u201cOne should not\u201d: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f7c\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span> (but not *<span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f61\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f7c\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span>)<\/li> <li>\u201cNot yet\u201d: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span> (but not *<span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f61\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span>)<\/li> <li>The imminent future: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span> and <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f61\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span><\/li> <li>\u201cTo have had the opportunity\u201d: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f56\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b<\/span> and <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f61\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f56\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b<\/span><\/li> <\/ul><p class=\"Paragraph\">In each of these last four cases, the corresponding egophoric forms may also be used.<\/p>","title":""}]}